BAHAMUT 3.0 — INSTALLATION GUIDE
=================================

DEPENDENCIES
------------
Bahamut requires a C11 compiler, Meson, Ninja, OpenSSL, and zlib.

Debian / Ubuntu:
    sudo apt-get install build-essential meson ninja-build pkg-config \
        libssl-dev zlib1g-dev

Fedora / RHEL:
    sudo dnf install gcc meson ninja-build pkg-config openssl-devel zlib-devel

FreeBSD:
    pkg install meson ninja pkgconf openssl

macOS (Homebrew):
    brew install meson ninja pkg-config openssl

Python 3 + pytest are needed only for the integration test suite:
    pip install pytest


BUILDING
--------
1.  Configure and build:

        meson setup build
        ninja -C build

    The compiled binary is at build/src/ircd.

2.  (Optional) Set build options:

        meson setup build -Dsocketengine=epoll -Dmaxconnections=65536
        ninja -C build

    Available options:
        socketengine    auto, epoll, kqueue, poll, select, devpoll
        maxconnections  Maximum simultaneous connections (default: 32768)
        hookmodules     Enable loadable modules (default: true)

3.  Install to a prefix:

        meson setup build --prefix=/usr/local/ircd
        ninja -C build
        ninja -C build install


CONFIGURATION
-------------
1.  Copy the template config:

        cp doc/template.conf /usr/local/ircd/ircd.conf

2.  Edit ircd.conf — at minimum set the server name, admin info, and ports.
    See doc/reference.conf for detailed documentation of every config block.

3.  Generate a TLS certificate (required for SSL ports and STARTTLS):

        openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:2048 -keyout ircd.key \
            -out ircd.crt -days 365 -nodes -subj "/CN=irc.example.com"

    Place the files in the server's working directory (or use absolute paths
    in the ssl {} config block).  For production, use a certificate from
    Let's Encrypt or another CA.


RUNNING
-------
    /usr/local/ircd/ircd

    # Or with an explicit config:
    /usr/local/ircd/ircd -f /path/to/ircd.conf

    # Run in the foreground (useful for debugging):
    /usr/local/ircd/ircd -t


TESTING
-------
    # Run the full integration test suite (51 tests)
    python3 -m pytest tests/ -v

    # Run a specific suite
    python3 -m pytest tests/suites/test_registration.py -v


UPGRADING FROM BAHAMUT 2.x
---------------------------
See doc/MIGRATION.md for a comprehensive migration guide covering:
  - Build system (autotools -> Meson)
  - Configuration changes (new blocks, removed options)
  - Server linking (TS5 connect{} -> gossip gopeer{})
  - TLS and IRCv3 features


Best of luck!
-The Bahamut Team
